(1) Any person who without lawful authority— (a) destroys, damages or removes any telecommunication apparatus ; (b) disturbs, obstructs or impedes in any way the free and proper use or working of any such apparatus or of any telecommunication system ; (c) wilfully intercepts or taps into any telecommunication not intended to be heard or received by him; (d) affixes or attaches any line, cable, wire, conductor or other thing to any such apparatus or system; or (e) wilfully interferes with or hinders the construction, alteration, restoration, maintenance or examination of any such system; shall be guilty of an offence and shall be liable on conviction to a fine not exceeding twenty thousand penalty units or to imprisonment for a term not exceeding six years, or to both: Provided that a person shall not be guilty of an offence by virtue of a contravention of paragraph (c) to the extent that the person's activities are authorised by or under any Act.
